15/08/2006
SARAJEVO, Bosnia and Herzegovina (BiH) -- Representatives of the BiH and Turkish governments sealed an agreement Monday (14 August) on bilateral co-operation in the fields of military training, technology and science.
The document provides for the exchange of information and experience, as well as equipment deliveries between the two countries.
BiH Deputy Defence Minister Enes Becirbasic stressed the significance of the deal, as Turkey is a member of NATO and BiH seeks membership in NATO's Partnership for Peace programme.
(PBS BiH - 14/08/06)
